reviews.text:
We were so excited to get some dessert after our dinner and this place looked great. Had good choices and big cakes.  We ordered a brownie, lemon bar, M&M chocolate chip cookie and a piece of carrot cake. All of them were less than mediocre. The lemon bar had very little flavor. They carrot cake had more frosting and bland cream cheese layers than anything. The cake was crumbly and dry. My kids would not finish the brownie or cookie. Atmosphere was really cool üòé and the people working there were very friendly.
Too bad the dessert was blah.
The staff was kind.  We stopped in for a warm up and everything was very good.  I appreciated the ceramic tableware, it felt like home.

Fantastic baked goods and food! Loved every single cake I've tried here. Always perfect flavor, texture, consistency, everything you would want from a cake. Can't go wrong with anything on the menu. Highly recommend this place.

A nice bakery and cafe with good food.  They seem to do a lot of locally sourced.  Plenty of seats between the bakery and cafe.  They don't have table service though.  Fun atmosphere.  Plan to spend about $12 / plate.

Makes one of my favorite Chai lattes. Tasty baked goods and yummy cafe options. Gurus is connected so you can enjoy other food options.
Update: we‚Äôve enjoyed the Delicious blueberry pancakes and a yummy cowboy eggs Benedict covered in country gravy. #enlitenbakery

detailedReviews.text: Friendly staff, great variety of options to choose from and super well priced. I'll eat here again when I'm back in Provo

detailedReviews.author: Meriah Kulikovskyi
detailedReviews.text: The bakery selection is decent, but just be warned that they will likely not have anyone manning the register so you'll have to wait in the line at gurus next door to be helped

detailedReviews.text: Fantastic baked goods and food! Loved every single cake I've tried here. Always perfect flavor, texture, consistency, everything you would want from a cake. Can't go wrong with anything on the menu. Highly recommend this place.

detailedReviews.author: Rachel Whitlock
detailedReviews.text: The chocolate cake is literally the best thing I‚Äôve ever tasted. Everyone must come here and try it.

detailedReviews.author: Kamberlyn Jensen
detailedReviews.text: Don't trust the Gluten Free menu!  Waited 25 minutes for our GF pizza's and they arrived definitely not gluten free, regular flour crust. It wasn't even busy.  When listening to them discuss it too many of them were confused with the gluten free option. Atleast I got my money back, but we are still hungry. We are very disappointed because we had even called ahead and asked about gluten free options

detailedReviews.author: B Reeves
detailedReviews.text: Enjoyable spot for breakfast in Provo‚Äôs historic district.

detailedReviews.author: Noah P
detailedReviews.text: The chocolate cake was fantastic. Great service, good prices, definitely coming back for more!

detailedReviews.author: Kyle Crowley
detailedReviews.text: Great breakfast and the staff was super friendly.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Binkley
detailedReviews.text:
Enliten is a small, cozy coffee shop located in the heart of downtown Provo, Utah. The shop has a warm and inviting atmosphere, with exposed brick walls, well-lit windows, and eclectic art on the walls. The staff is friendly and accommodating, and they are always happy to help you find the perfect cup of coffee.

If you're looking for a great cup of coffee in a warm and inviting atmosphere, I would recommend stopping by. I grabbed a rooibos tea and treat on the way home. (Also a fun art print for cheap)

detailedReviews.author: Erik
detailedReviews.text: One of the better places I‚Äôve had recently and very reasonably priced.

detailedReviews.author: Maxwell Lloyd
detailedReviews.text: Amazing bakery 10/10, and very reasonable prices!

detailedReviews.author: Robby Dubbs
detailedReviews.text: Good service, cool environment, and some of the best hot chocolate I have ever had. Definitely hit the spot after walking around in the rain in downtown provo haha. Seating was a little tight but everything else was great.

detailedReviews.author: Sage Sandstrom
detailedReviews.text: I had a bit of bloating/stomach ache but the chicken pesto sandwich was so good I ate the whole thing anyway, no regrets

detailedReviews.author: Jacob Selman
detailedReviews.text:
Trash service.
I went in this morning for a single cup of coffee. After waiting about 10 minutes nothing was made. Thanks for the refund and enjoy your tip.

detailedReviews.author: Jenn G
detailedReviews.text: There aren‚Äôt many dine in dessert places in Utah Valley. We decided to try dessert here and it‚Äôs a hidden gem. Their PB cake was so delicious and their carrot cake was moist and yummy! This will be our new go to place! It‚Äôs also a delicious lunch or dinner spot. Servers were so friendly. Sorry no photos, we dove in too fast to taste the yummy dessert.

detailedReviews.author: Holland
detailedReviews.text: Best French toast I‚Äôve ever had and the vibes in here are wonderful

detailedReviews.author: Michael .Rotter
detailedReviews.text: Extremely hit or miss. Somedays they make great coffee other days not so great. We got two americanos recently and we are pretty sure they just reused the grounds for each espresso shot. It was disgusting. They could do better barista training.

detailedReviews.author: Tanya Wadley
detailedReviews.text: Great value. We had a piece of chocolate peanut butter cake. It was delicious and huge, and only $4. They had a great selection of treats. I can't say anything about the food, except they are owned and operated by the owner of Guru's and have many exact menu items. There are so many Provo Gems in the restaurant category and seem priced better than Salt Lake restaurants.

detailedReviews.author: Luke Buteyn-Soeby
detailedReviews.text: Good fun,  great desserts,  and a really nice atmosphere.  Love the artwork and sculptures!

detailedReviews.author: Kiko Lian
detailedReviews.text: It's a pretty nice place to hang around and the coffee isn't bad. The staff will often bring their kids behind the counter and they put ungloved hands to grab pastries for themselves from the back. So I don't really order the pastries here during covid times especially.

detailedReviews.author: Sasha ‚ÄúSass‚Äù J
detailedReviews.text: The place looks great but unfortunately it seems like the cook was having a pretty bad day. We ordered the artichoke, spinach and mushroom pizza, and it arrived without mushrooms. When we asked for it to be corrected, the cook handed us a little tub of RAW mushrooms. Then we approached a waitress and asked for a better solution. She took our pizza to put it back in the oven, and brought it back at room temperature still with mostly raw mushrooms. We gave up at that point and enjoyed the spinach artichoke pizza. Oh well. Hopefully the chef has a better day next time.

detailedReviews.author: James Boone
detailedReviews.text: We were helped by Logan. He was very helpful and friendly.  This is a great bakery

detailedReviews.author: Steve G
detailedReviews.text: The breakfast mess is really good. It's really hard to find a good and healthy breakfast in Utah County. I was very impressed with the food.

detailedReviews.author: Mary Beth Gray
detailedReviews.text: This place was so adorable. Come for the coffee, stay for the chocolate chip cookies üòç

detailedReviews.author: Scott Sharp
detailedReviews.text: Unbelievably slow. Over an hour and still haven't received our two sandwiches to go. Shame! Do t go unless you plan on spending the day there.

detailedReviews.author: Kat L
detailedReviews.text: A special stop for my daughter‚Äôs birthday during the pandemic in the heat of summer for a fruity Italian soda with whipped cream. Staff answered all our questions well and were so nice. Daughter also enjoyed a birthday almond croissant we brought home the next day, would come back for more treats!

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Olmstead
detailedReviews.text: Enliten is the perfect place to go and enjoy a nice cup of coffee. Atmosphere is very relaxed, and the staff is always very helpful and provide good service. A personal favorite!

detailedReviews.author: tenaya gappmayer
detailedReviews.text: So disappointed to get stuff to go and not receive what I ordered. I guess my fault for not double checking.

detailedReviews.author: Daniel Poulson
detailedReviews.text: Nice atmosphere. The food and drinks are just fine, not great.

detailedReviews.author: Amber Moran
detailedReviews.text: What a great find! We're in town visiting from California. After all the Thanksgiving food we were looking for something a bit lighter. I have to say that I'm definitely a carnivore but this all veggie omelette wrap was amazing! All the staff was friendly and the coffee was good to boot. Will keep this on the short list for the next visit.

detailedReviews.author: Belinda Purdum
detailedReviews.text:
Little bakery attached to Guru‚Äôs. A great fit because you can eat a healthy lunch and then go right next door for dessert and coffee. Guru‚Äôs and Enliten have been the go-to meet up spot downtown for a number of years now.

WiFi. Counter serve. Minimal street parking, but it‚Äôs only busy during certain times. Garage parking nearby. Lots of seating, a few couches and plug-in spots. Only a block away from the best spots for a downtown stroll.

detailedReviews.author: Kameron Barkle
detailedReviews.text: Came to try some things from their bakery. I tried the ham and cheese croissant and their Nutella brownie. They were both tasty, but I was a little disappointed with the small amount of ham and cheese inside the croissant, and somehow I lost half my brownie when the cashier put it in the box. I don't know what really happened there but the brownie was definitely bigger than this when he pulled it out of the tray.

detailedReviews.author: Marissa Johnson
detailedReviews.text: I went here for a brunch/coffee date. This is a really charming place. It has a really nice vibe to it. The coffee is pretty darn good, as is the food. I definitely recommend this place.

detailedReviews.author: Wilma Flores
detailedReviews.text: The staff is always super nice and polite and we always have a laugh. I will always recommend them to a friend.Cute little cafe attached to Gurus next door. Their giant cinnamon and orange rolls are the perfect treat to share! A great place to get some work done or catch up with friends. Don't forget to tip your staff! They work HARD!

detailedReviews.author: Grant Evans
detailedReviews.text: They are slow at taking your order.

detailedReviews.author: Kelsey Henry
detailedReviews.text: Fast service and friendly staff. A great option when you're looking for something delicious and a bit on the healthier side--well, that is unless you get the sweet potato fries, which you should because they're delicious!

detailedReviews.author: Jessie Hensley
detailedReviews.text: This place has a pretty cool environment nice place to chill and drink coffee

detailedReviews.author: Benjamin Dent
detailedReviews.text: Awesome spot in Provo! If you want to hang out with fake california wannabe hipsters, go to peace on earth coffee

detailedReviews.author: Ivy Grace
detailedReviews.text: They took 30 minutes on my salad which i was bugged by because it was so slow. Then i get home and my whole order is wrong. I made it specifically for my own health issues with certain food and they included everything i said i couldn't eat. Im very disappointed. I've been going here for years and this is the first time they've fuked up. Next time, read the receipts so you don't get angry customers.

detailedReviews.author: Kathy Miller
detailedReviews.text: We've visited this place a few times for breakfast and brunch and have really enjoyed it. We still have to try quite a few things from their menu, but I'll say I loved the Almond Croissant  and their lemon cake. My husband has also tried one of their burritos and the Huevos Rancheros and  liked both.  Staff was also nice both times we've been there. We'll be back

detailedReviews.author: Anney Germaine
detailedReviews.text: The Chai Latte was AMAZING! Cute place, lots of options, good drinks.

detailedReviews.author: Bonita H
detailedReviews.text: This cafe has awesome vibes. It‚Äôs an extension of Guru, but it has its own unique space. The coffee is great and the chocolate chip cookies are gooey and delicious!

detailedReviews.author: zachary clarke
detailedReviews.text: They said the cheesecake was good and they were right.  Only two kinds, but way worth the trip.  Also, the food was a good price for a large quantity.  I'm Satisfied with my experience.

detailedReviews.author: Ilizibith Summerhalder
detailedReviews.text: Great coffee, tea, food, and pastries. I usually get a coffee or tea and a cookie, and it's so cheap for the quality. Also, the open mic poetry night they host every Thursday is always a good time.

detailedReviews.author: Phillip Nako
detailedReviews.text: Great atmosphere.

detailedReviews.author: American Spirit
detailedReviews.text: Gluten free cookies üç™üòâ

detailedReviews.author: Doug William
detailedReviews.text: Service is slow in the bakery.

detailedReviews.author: Paul Crenshaw
detailedReviews.text: I'm not a huge fan of their employees, but the sandwiches have been worth the visits.

detailedReviews.author: M. Harding
detailedReviews.text: Good coffee and service. Nice to have a coffee shop open late in Provo.

detailedReviews.author: Pamela Lane
detailedReviews.text: I really want to give this place a better review because there is a lot of potential this place could have. I have never had a positive experience between Gurus and Enliten Cafe. I never go there by choice I only go there if friends or family want to go. Unfortunarly, in the span of a week the company I was with on two separate occasions wanted to go here. The first time I ordered the Huevos Rancheros and was pretty disappointed how it was made. Its pretty obvious they use minute rice. There were next to no beans on the dish as well. Are they that cheap!? Waaaay too much cheese on top, I can see the potential of this dish had they used better ingredients and less cheese as well as better quality of cheese. It is clear that only laziness, cutting corners to save money, and carelessness went into making the dish.  The second occasion I went I ordered the Benny. I waited OVER 40 MINUTES to get my meal in a cafe that only had 4 people in it at 9am. The place was not busy whatsoever. There were at least 5 employees NOT one even cared to check up on us. Finally after getting pretty frustrated I went and waited on someone to help me at the front counter. After the 2 emoloyees got done with their conversation one of them finally approached me. I said I had been waiting a very long time for my meal and people that had showed up well after me were recieving their meals. I'm pretty frustrated I did not get compensated for the time they wasted out of my morning. I'm even more frustrated about the overall lack of professionalism and laziness of the business. Whoever manages this place you really need to step it up. It really amazes me that I waited that long and if I hadn't gone to check on my food who knows how much longer I would have waited. Instruct your employess on customer service perhaps instruct yourself too. It's a SERVICE oriented business...2 solid thumbs down. I regret tipping beforehand.

detailedReviews.author: Shale C
detailedReviews.text:
Apr 2018 Edit: The last time I went, I got half a sandwich and a small cup of tomato basil soup. (the cup is smaller than a bowl). When I asked the server to double check to see if they were supposed to only give me a cup he told me yes. I was very upset as a couple months ago I was told that a "half and half" combo meal means a sandwich and a BOWL of soup, not a CUP.

I feel that for only half a sandwich (not even a full sandwich I'm supposed to have) and a cup of soup,  $12 is a steep price to pay. I will probably never go back.
-------
I come here almost every Friday. They are slightly pricey for soup and sandwich, but this is the Best Tomato Basil soup I have ever had. The artisan foccia bread on their sandwich is a little dry, but that's fixed with dipping it in to the soup. The inside of the sandwich (caprese cheese) is A plus. I also love their cobb salad. So 4 stars on the food.

However, I don't stay for the food. I stay for the atmosphere and the ambience of the cafe. And the half price bakery goods after 5. I love the free WiFi, and if nothing strikes your food fancy, you can also order from Guru's at the Enliten counter. 5 stars for atmosphere.

Probably a 3.5 for service. Sometimes I've ordered a combo, yet got a tiny cup of soup rather than a bowl. I know better now, but when it happened I was confused but went with it. Sometimes theb staff seem confused on what you do or do not have, even though you have a number sign.

(As an aside, they have diet dr. pepper!!)

detailedReviews.author: C S
detailedReviews.text: The food was pretty good, but the customer service was horrible! I waited 20 minutes for a salad, that was sitting there the entire time. For some reason, my food didn‚Äôt have a ticket so they just left it there. After waiting for so long, I finally went up and asked if the food on the counter was mine. The person who helped me was extremely nice and he apologized. However, the rest of the staff was unprofessional. I kept signaling to the girl with pink hair and she refused to help me. So disappointed overall!

detailedReviews.author: Chani
detailedReviews.text: So yummy!

detailedReviews.author: Sieben Smoot
detailedReviews.text: Got a Reuben here and there bread for it was amazing! The rest was good too, but the bread... Wow! Oh, and they have hazelnut Italian soda, which i love!

detailedReviews.author: Brent Stratton
detailedReviews.text: A nice bakery and cafe with good food.  They seem to do a lot of locally sourced.  Plenty of seats between the bakery and cafe.  They don't have table service though.  Fun atmosphere.  Plan to spend about $12 / plate.

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth Bat-Sarah
detailedReviews.text: Delicious veggie bowl over brown rice. Proper cappuccino. Plenty of space for solo diners.

detailedReviews.author: Whitney Call Meek
detailedReviews.text: I love the atmosphere of this bakery and often frequent Enliten and Guru's--my last visit, however, was extremely disappointing. I asked for a sandwich with light mustard, which resulted in a sandwich that was filled to the brim with mustard, it was all I could taste. Worse, still, I specifically ordered a dairy-free hot chocolate since I am lactose intolerant. The hot chocolate was delicious, but ten minutes after I got home, I spent the next 30 minutes vomiting my entire meal, which only happens after I consume dairy. I try not to be too picky at restaurants, but both requests I'd made at my last visit were ignored.

detailedReviews.author: Ji Eun Park
detailedReviews.text: Great food, not too pricy. Excellent atmosphere and very friendly staff.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Moore
detailedReviews.text: Great lunch, breakfast and dinner items with some of the best pastries in the state.

detailedReviews.author: Jason Bloomberg
detailedReviews.text:
Co-Located with Guru's Cafe in Provo, it shares some of the same aesthetics.  I "checked in" on YELP at Guru's when we had dinner there and was "rewarded" with a coupon for a "free cookie" from Enliten Bakery.  Normally, I don't accept gifts or discounts from places I review unless it is a printed coupon anyone can use and this offer seemed close enough to that standard to give it a try.  Also, living hundreds of miles away there was not likely another opportunity to use it later.  Generally, my view is if I wouldn't buy something, getting it for free with a coupon is "no great deal."

It was a busy day for the hard working crew at Enlighten and Guru's and it was also within an hour of their closing.  After enjoying a very good dinner I went to the bakery counter to find out what my coupon could redeem?  They had a single peanut butter cookie left which had a corner broken off, some sugar cookies, and some gluten-free cookies, one each of chocolate chip, the other was Snickerdoodle. Of all of these the broken peanut butter cookie was the most appealing to me and sugar cookies the least. I also thought to myself I'll take "the damaged one" so they can sell the others.  The nice lady grabbed it with tongs and just add she tried to put it in a bag with them the cookie fell to the floor.  She was mortified.  She asked if I wanted a suggest cookie instead and I explained that would not go over well with my wife who would be sharing it with me.  She then offered the two remaining gluten-free cookies, which I accepted. The grace she handled this with is more noteworthy than the cookies.

They were good, even two days later when we enjoyed them with decaf enhanced with a little Irish Cream back at home.

The bakery also had Sweet Potato Cheesecake which really intrigued me but I didn't have room for after our meal from Guru's and our would not have kept well during our drive back to Cheyenne the next day.

While we were still a at the bakery,  I  "checked in" on YELP and... got another coupon for a "free cookie".  The next time were there I'm not going to use it. Instead, I'm going to leave room for desert and try a slice of that Sweet Potato (or some other) cheesecake. üòÅ

detailedReviews.text: Really comfortable place the people are nice

detailedReviews.author: Lynden Jensen
detailedReviews.text: Not worth the price.
